derstood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret Adelby was born about 1318, in England, United Kingdom, her father, William Adelby, was 30 and her mother, Margaret Carbonel, was 25. She had at least 1 son with Thomas Boteler."},"et":{"about 1318–":"umbes 1318–Surnud","1318–Female":"1318–Surnud","1317–1393":"1317–1393","1370–1429":"1370–1429","1290–Male":"1290–Surnud","1295–Female":"1295–Surnud","about 1318":"umbes 1318","before 1370":"enne 1370","1295":"1295","1393":"1393","1370":"1370","1429":"1429","1318":"1318","1290":"1290","1317":"1317","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1318–":"noin 1318–Kuollut","1318–Female":"1318–Kuollut","1317–1393":"1317–1393","1370–1429":"1370–1429","1290–Male":"1290–Kuollut","1295–Female":"1295–Kuollut","about 1318":"noin 1318","before 1370":"ennen vuotta 1370","1295":"1295","1393":"1393","1370":"1370","1429":"1429","1318":"1318","1290":"1290","1317":"1317","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1318–":"environ 1318–Décédée","1318–Female":"1318–Décédée","1317–1393":"1317–1393","1370–1429":"